eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable

Class AbstractImmutableCollectionWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable.AbstractImmutableCollectionWrapper<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImmutableCollection<T>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImmutableListWrapper, ImmutableSetWrapper

    public abstract class AbstractImmutableCollectionWrapper<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ImmutableCollection<T>
    An immutable collection. It wraps a java.util.Collection, but does not implement java.util.Collection .
    The real collection can be further modified by any one who holds it, but not by this interface. Casting to the real collection is impossible at compilation time.
    Author:
    Asher Stern
